HEADWORD: Ouananiche
<hw>Oua`na`niche"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Canadian F., of
Amer. Indian origin.]</ety> <def>A small landlocked variety of the
Atlantic salmon (<spn>Salmo salar ounaniche</spn>) of Lake St. John,
Canada, and neighboring waters, noted for its vigor and activity, and
habit of leaping from the water when hooked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

